nodes.title: Auto Segmented Masks (ignore if not using Loops &&)
How to make loops
widgets_values:
To make a loop:

1- Write in your prompt two or more prompts separated by "&&" (without quotation marks).
2- Each prompt will be assigned to a segmented mask in the mask order previwed here. 
3- Run the workflow. It will generate a number of images equal to the number of segmented masks/prompts. It will generate a whole image for each mask/loop so each prompt is its own thing. It works with "area inpainting" and everything else, but "outpainting" is not recommended because it will outpaint for each segmented mask, which makes no sense. Best to outpaint first and inpaint with loops after it.

IF you have batch bigger than 1 AND The "Image Chooser" (located on the "Loops Compositing" group, near the end) turned ON, you need to pick each image of each step. You can also leave it off and the first image of each step will be selected.

4- Finally, your composite image will be saved.

nodes.title: Notes on segmented masks for loops
widgets_values:
Loops are only triggered IF you have multiple prompts on the main prompt devided by "&&". If not, these segmented masks won't be used.

You can check how many segmented masks (cyan preview) was devided into automatically. 

Masks are segmented automatically following this order: always right to left first, then up to down... →↓

nodes.title: Notes on Loop prompts and Shedule LoRas
widgets_values:
Workflow allows your prompt to have additional LoRa syntax directly written on it, and if using loops, each loop can have its own lora by doing this.

Read about LoRa schedule syntax here: https://github.com/asagi4/comfyui-prompt-control/blob/master/doc/syntax.md

Exemple Write it on the positive prompt: <lora:Shrek:0.7> [<lora:tattoo_flux:0.8>::0.4]

This will have Shrek LoRA applied at 0.7 strength throughout the generation, while tattoo_flux will be applied at 0.8 strength until 40% of the generation, after which tattoo_flux will be removed.

Keep in mind, adding or removing LoRas with schedule have an impact in the generation time.

LoRas added by the group (LoRas - Optional) will be ALWAYS On at all the time on all the loops.
